column5: Went out at Innisfil park and was able to fish 60-70 FOW for the whities and lakers. Went 1 for 4 on whities using a small williams.  ICE THICKNESS WAS FROM 4"-6" of hard black ice. Marked a ton but not many takers today. Sorry no pics this time. Play safe out there this weekend.  Rustic
Good going!   Thanks for the heads up on the ice conditions.  blyght
Great News !...  That is where the Meet and Greet in aid of Tyler is being held on Feb 24...  Motv8tr will be pleased...

That's great news about the ice conditions, and with this cold weather there should be plenty by the 24th   Sorry you didn't do better in the catching dept. but that just means they're waiting for the 24th  Knotaclue, the parking lot at the park is pretty much always open, so you should have no worries there.  Maureen
Thanks fer the report. I imagine it was a cold day. Today is very mild, in comparison, and I think it will affect the bite in a positive way.
thanks for the report ...glad to hear the ice conditions are improving big time from 1 week ago...looking forward to getting out real soon....cheers
I was close to there today and got a full cooler. How do I donate a prize to this Tyler charity?
